Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.91,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,FAMOUS DETECTIVE HOLMES
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.06,0:01:41.02,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Castle!\NHolmes, Dead or Alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.87,0:01:44.17,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,The Holy Cross Sword...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.81,0:01:46.64,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,...after thirty years,\Nit's open to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.64,0:01:47.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The noble Wizard family...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.84,0:01:50.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,they even sat at the same dinner table\Nwith King Arthur in the old days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.48,0:01:53.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They handed down this mysterious\Ntreasured sword to their descendants.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.05,0:01:56.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Holmes, are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.82,0:01:59.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Holy Cross Sword is\Na symbol of aristocracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.19,0:02:01.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And it has a very important\Nsecret sealed inside of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.99,0:02:03.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:08.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a rumour about the secret.\NIt could lead to an enormous treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.00,0:02:15.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.84,0:02:21.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Since such an important treasure will\Nbe open to the public, tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.91,0:02:23.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it's time\Nfor you to relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.11,0:02:26.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, until tomorrow, they're\Nplanning to have security guards...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.52,0:02:28.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,and the sword will be\Nkept in a large safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.52,0:02:31.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?\NHow do you know so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.39,0:02:34.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, a messenger from\Nthe Wizard family came by earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.26,0:02:35.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.96,0:02:38.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?\NI didn't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.46,0:03:15.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.12,0:03:35.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.42,0:03:39.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.66,0:04:47.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this really is a marvellous sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.96,0:04:50.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The jewels and ornaments\Nare so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.03,0:04:52.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This workmanship...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.16,0:04:54.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been crafted almost five\Nhundred years ago or even earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:04:58.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But why have they sealed this\Ninside of a triangle crystal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.43,0:05:00.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.10,0:05:02.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.51,0:05:05.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Mr. Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.34,0:05:10.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Wizard, It's been a long time.\NLittle Sir William, how are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.15,0:05:13.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my friend, Watson.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:14.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.79,0:05:16.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.32,0:05:22.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you do?\NWilly, can you greet our guests, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.89,0:05:24.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Watson, it's nice to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.76,0:05:26.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How come you have such sharp ears?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:30.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Does this mean there's\Na case going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.47,0:05:33.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you didn't know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.27,0:05:38.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, a mysterious incident\Nrecently occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.11,0:05:39.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mysterious incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:45.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Holy Cross Sword\Nwas kept in this safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.58,0:05:51.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,However, yesterday, some thief\Nbroke in and opened the safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.62,0:05:53.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see,\Nhe didn't steal the sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:57.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Is there any other\Njewellery inside the safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:59.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, only the Holy Cross Sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.03,0:06:04.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The thief's target was the sword,\Nbut the sword was not taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.77,0:06:06.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of such\Na ridiculous story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.01,0:06:13.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Did they replace the sword\Nwith a forgery?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.48,0:06:15.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so at first...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.31,0:06:19.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,but this is the real sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.25,0:06:23.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm going to\Ninvestigate elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.82,0:06:25.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let you investigate here,\NMr. Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.26,0:06:29.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Nyah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.96,0:06:32.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.63,0:06:38.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It's magnesium.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.57,0:06:39.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Magnesium? What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.80,0:06:40.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.74,0:06:42.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The stuff that creates a flash\Nwhen you take a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.81,0:06:46.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did they only take a picture\Nand leave the sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.48,0:06:55.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,May I see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.66,0:07:04.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I can see some\Nsmall hieroglyphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.63,0:07:10.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.66,0:07:33.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.36,0:07:38.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The first one is a snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.16,0:07:43.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The next symbol is three lumps\Nand two shiny eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.40,0:07:44.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And a castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.37,0:07:46.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There are seven symbols all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.94,0:07:49.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If you figure out what they mean,\Nyou will know the secret of the sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.87,0:07:55.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the legend of a treasure\Nhidden by our ancestors is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.95,0:07:58.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Professor wanted to take\Na picture of these symbols.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.85,0:08:08.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The legend was written in the ancient\Ncode of the Wizard family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.50,0:08:14.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is wrong with this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.77,0:08:18.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing on the photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.90,0:08:19.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's shouldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.40,0:08:21.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.78,0:08:32.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We took out the sword and\Nprojected the symbols on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.21,0:08:34.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we took a picture of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.75,0:08:35.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.95,0:08:40.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You fools!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.26,0:08:43.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you burned magnesium,\Nthe symbols didn't show up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.06,0:08:48.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't take a picture unless\Nwe use a magnesium flash.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.10,0:08:50.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We just followed your instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.97,0:08:55.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. How could I make the mistake of\Ngiving this mission to these two fools?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:08:58.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, then it wasn't our mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.71,0:08:59.54,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.61,0:09:00.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.51,0:09:01.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.51,0:09:03.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You two! Just remember what\Nkind of symbols they were!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.01,0:09:04.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.18,0:09:05.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.98,0:09:06.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a snake!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.88,0:09:08.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And its tail was split in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.68,0:09:10.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,First, the snake,\Nis of course... a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.72,0:09:13.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the two tails are...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.62,0:09:15.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,the joining point of two\Nof the river's branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.26,0:09:20.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the three lumps\Nare mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.90,0:09:24.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes and the two shiny eyes\Nare either lakes or swamps.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.67,0:09:26.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now let's put all of these\Non the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.14,0:09:32.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Dayburg Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.51,0:09:34.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the ancestral home\Nof the Wizard family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.71,0:09:36.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we just have\Nto visit this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.61,0:09:40.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to Dayburg Castle\Nimmediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.40,0:09:55.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They saved us the time\Nof figuring this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.46,0:09:58.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's follow them and steal the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.39,0:10:19.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The clouds are very close.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.96,0:10:21.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It might rain soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.83,0:10:24.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.49,0:10:25.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You found me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.23,0:10:27.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.23,0:10:32.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They've stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.37,0:10:35.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't just come\Nalong with us like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.34,0:10:39.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I left a letter for my grandfather.\NSo, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.54,0:10:40.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.85,0:10:46.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,it's all right.\NI'm already old enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.58,0:10:49.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you promise that you won't\Ndo anything dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.85,0:10:51.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.89,0:10:53.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.02,0:10:55.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.66,0:10:57.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do anything dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.13,0:11:01.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, they started to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.40,0:11:03.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They're trying to get ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.57,0:11:05.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It will soon be daybreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.98,0:11:21.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Dayburg Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.05,0:11:25.35,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.\NThree mountains and two lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.57,0:11:47.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Get to the basement quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.34,0:11:49.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the basement?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.35,0:11:50.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.65,0:11:54.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an old custom to hide\Ntreasure inside a basement!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.49,0:11:59.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stone circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.62,0:12:03.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's shaped like a necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.96,0:12:05.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry!\NIt's almost sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.51,0:12:20.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.54,0:12:23.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure some scary\Nghost will come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.51,0:12:26.54,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Humph! Ridiculous! I won't share\Nany treasure with you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.60,0:12:41.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.53,0:12:45.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.17,0:12:47.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! It's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.81,0:12:50.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.67,0:12:51.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,As usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.70,0:13:18.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The one piece of rock that\Nthe sunrise points to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.37,0:13:19.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.74,0:13:22.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! "Two people who have good\Nsouls should help each other."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:24.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,"Go backward one step\Nand then go forward."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.57,0:13:28.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to move this rock\Nwith just two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.97,0:13:57.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:01.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and open this!\NHold this rock!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.81,0:14:05.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice but to use force.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.96,0:14:21.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.60,0:14:23.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.38,0:14:37.64,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are these holes for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.71,0:14:39.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We should be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.25,0:14:43.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.05,0:14:45.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watson!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.70,0:14:57.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.78,0:15:15.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.33,0:15:28.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.06,0:15:30.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.73,0:15:34.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like there is a\Ntunnel over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.64,0:15:38.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch your step.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.34,0:15:40.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I'm at\Nthe bottom of a well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.41,0:15:44.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not good!\NLet's go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.02,0:15:53.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.59,0:15:57.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now there's water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.49,0:15:59.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Water from the lake is pouring in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.40,0:16:08.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Holmes! Do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.70,0:16:11.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We will all drown if we stay here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.61,0:16:14.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Just hang on until the\Nwater reaches the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.28,0:16:20.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.\NGoodbye my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.35,0:16:26.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watson!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.87,0:16:40.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,My rival, Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.54,0:16:43.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange meeting each other\Nin such an unusual place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.37,0:16:44.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you look awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.74,0:16:47.64,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the end of\Nthe famous detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.71,0:16:49.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I humbly pray that your soul\Nrests in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.42,0:17:03.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We're saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.66,0:17:06.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Moriarty's\Nnew weapon saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.68,0:17:25.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous!\NThis stone bridge looks very fragile.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.05,0:17:27.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It can handle my weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.52,0:17:30.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Secure the end of the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.93,0:17:41.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.13,0:17:43.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.50,0:17:46.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.89,0:18:04.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watson!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.42,0:18:35.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Willy, the hole!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.92,0:19:09.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.42,0:19:11.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the treasure inside of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.22,0:19:13.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.27,0:19:27.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.50,0:19:29.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like an old bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.47,0:19:30.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.61,0:19:34.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! The place where they hid the\Ntreasure, must be written in this bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.31,0:19:35.14,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.81,0:19:39.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's there!\NIt's just a bible!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.05,0:19:41.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Drat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.32,0:19:44.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! Somebody\Nmust've already stolen it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.75,0:19:46.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.96,0:19:50.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody's coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.69,0:19:53.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice but to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.21,0:20:05.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!\NThey got here first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.28,0:20:13.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The treasure is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.62,0:20:16.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there wasn't any\Ntreasure to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.92,0:20:19.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,See, only the mark left by the bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.09,0:20:21.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,One bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.36,0:20:26.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Moriarty got\Nangry and threw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.13,0:20:28.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.17,0:20:39.14,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.24,0:20:40.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.62,0:20:54.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.99,0:20:59.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What a beautiful bible!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.54,0:21:14.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the treasure that the\Nancestors of the Wizard family...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.48,0:21:17.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,left for their next generation,\N700 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.86,0:21:30.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.56,0:21:34.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa! I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.73,0:21:39.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I found your treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.07,0:21:42.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.91,0:21:50.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Curse you, Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.11,0:21:52.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I was waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.02,0:21:57.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Moriarty, this is your last day!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.35,0:22:00.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.10,0:22:17.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
